Method Detail

getResultString

public java.lang.String getResultString()
Returns the result string after applying the XSLT transformation. The first time this method is called the transformed result string is cached and subsequent calls to this method will return the cached result. If the transform cannot be performed the error cause is logged and the original result string is returned instead.

Specified by:
getResultString in interface TestResult
